To ensure adequate sleep, he said, the "secret weapon" of all students should be against stress, fatigue, and anxiety, and to prevent weight gain, since sleep deprivation puts the brain in starvation mode, leaving them hungry all the time.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old student in California studying chemical and physical biology, helped Professor Czeisler design the course.
