He stressed the importance of pre-maintenance prevention of bats in the holdings, as the unintentional destruction of a single nesting site could kill up to 400 females and young animals and wipe out the entire population.
Bats are protected and it is illegal to kill, harass or destroy them or their nesting sites.
Elisabeth Ferrell, a Scottish official with the Bat Conservation Trust, encouraged the community to help.
